<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36148d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36148d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36148d"> 148(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> necessariea not needed / still paying off</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On the other hand, there may be some families living in clean and tidy houses who are from one cause or another <mark>without the necessaries</mark> for physical efficiency, although their incomes are not so low as to place them below the primary poverty line. For instance, <mark>they may still be paying off some debt</mark> contracted at a time when the wage-earner was out of work. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 150</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09086f" href="c09all.htm#c09086f">VI.C.09:086(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
